::MC1::
What does incremental SfM reconstruction do?
{
= Adds views step by step
~ Uses only one image
~ Ignores new views
~ Compresses histograms
}

::MC2::
What does triangulation do in SfM?
{
= Computes new 3D points
~ Removes outliers
~ Normalizes brightness
~ Smooths histograms
}

::MC3::
What does bundle adjustment optimize?
{
= Poses and 3D points
~ Only focal length
~ Only 2D points
~ Only depth maps
}

::MC4::
What error does bundle adjustment minimize?
{
= Reprojection error
~ JPEG artifacts
~ Histogram bins
~ PCA variance
}

::MC5::
What type of problem is bundle adjustment?
{
= Nonlinear optimization
~ Linear filtering
~ Fourier transform
~ Histogram equalization
}

::MC6::
What is required for bundle adjustment to work well?
{
= Good initialization
~ Random guesses
~ Noise only
~ No correspondences
}

::MC7::
Why is bundle adjustment expensive?
{
= Many parameters optimized jointly
~ Only uses one point
~ Histogram computation
~ Audio filtering
}

::MC8::
What does loop closure address?
{
= Drift in reconstructions
~ Noise in histograms
~ Only brightness errors
~ Always exact results
}

::MC9::
Which is a challenge in SfM refinement?
{
= Local minima
~ Always robust
~ No scaling
~ Guaranteed convergence
}

